messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Reading (though more like teeth...)
messages.msgSnippet: ... Tim lost his front top two teeth in an accident when he was 2, and ate apples on the core and corn on the cob until he lost his bottom teeth, too
messages.messageBody:
4/4/03 21:43:

> Ds has both bottom front teeth in but not
> the top. One finally broke through this week. He'd been toothless for a
> year. At this rate maybe by the end of this summer he'll be able to eat corn
> on the cob without cutting it off. ;-)

Tim lost his front top two teeth in an accident when he was 2, and ate
apples on the core and corn on the cob until he lost his bottom teeth, too
(naturally, thank goodness!). I have no idea how he did it. He's finally
getting one of his permanent top teeth, but it's been 4 years with a gappy
smile.

Last Christmas, before the top tooth cut, he sang "All I want for Christmas
is My Two Front Teeth" in the Military Theatre's Christmas show, and was too
cute. They cast him as the youngest boy just so he could sing that song!

brenda
